  "texts": [
    "We apply these defense on our attacked images and evaluate on adversarial samples surrogated by SD15.",
    "Throughout this section, \"PCA-\" and \"ours-\" refer to minimize the L KL (consistent with Tab.",
    "I) with v = 1 × 10 -8; \"PCA+\" and \"ours+\" refer to maximize the L KL with v = 1.In the subsequent tables, bold text denotes the best results, arrows (↑/↓) indicate whether higher or lower values represent better protection performance.",
    "\"clean\" for each prompt is the IQA computed between clean image x and edited clean image f (x).",
    "Image Editing Results with Varied PromptsOur extensive experimentation is consistent with the hypothesis: PCA+ is good at Objective 1, while PCA-excels in addressing Objective 2."
